Changing the title from "Synchronization requires an update of the project" to

Unable to reproduce. I suspect you have some external (non-Eclipse) editor or
tool that is modifying that file. Eclipse doesn't know about changes made from
the outside unless you explicitly perform a refresh. You can also try turning on
auto-refresh (Preferences > Workbench > Refresh workspace automatically). Even
with auto-refresh, there is a delay before Eclipse will discover external changes.
